      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity with von Mises yield criterion; justified by published Ti-6Al-4V characterization data and prior validation studies.",
      "rationale": "The constitutive model selection (bilinear isotropic hardening, von Mises) is consistent with published literature for Ti-6Al-4V under quasi-static loading. Frictional contact at the screw-rod interface uses a Coulomb model with coefficient 0.22, consistent with measured values for anodized titanium surfaces. Model form uncertainty is bounded by the ensemble spread across three independent FEA implementations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of production-lot Ti-6Al-4V; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of test articles.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa ± 3.2 GPa, 1σ), yield strength (880 MPa ± 18 MPa, 1σ), and tangent modulus were derived from uniaxial tensile testing of production-lot coupons. Screw and rod geometry were confirmed by CMM measurement of five articles per lot. Input uncertainty distributions were propagated through the UQ analysis using Latin hypercube sampling (N=500 runs). A screening sensitivity study was documented in the UQ report narrative, identifying elastic modulus and friction coefficient as the dominant contributors to output variance; however, the full structured sensitivity analysis dataset was not separately encoded in this credibility package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs from production-representative lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to drawing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from production-representative lots and tested across two independent laboratories. CMM dimensional inspection confirmed all screws and rods were within drawing tolerances. Lot traceability was maintained throughout."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "ASTM F1717 protocol; testing at a single load rate of 5 mm/min; ambient temperature and humidity controlled.",
      "rationale": "Testing followed ASTM F1717 at a single crosshead displacement rate of 5 mm/min under ambient laboratory conditions. Only one test condition (load rate) was evaluated; rate-dependence of the quasi-static response was not characterized. This factor falls one gradation below the required level, representing a known gap acknowledged in the decision record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs derived directly from measured test article properties and test machine records; no surrogate or assumed values for primary QoI drivers.",
      "rationale": "All simulation input parameters were mapped directly to measured values from the test articles and test machine calibration records. Fixture geometry, grip compliance, and crosshead displacement were replicated in the simulation boundary conditions. No surrogate material data were used for the primary QoI drivers."
    },
